People are desperate for games considering all the recent failures and low amount of quality AAA games to choose from and fact that it's F2P all the hype and downloads isn't so surprising.

I see another hyped and very commercial battle royale mode nothing special here just another cash grab and it's very telling when you have devs politically pandering. 

This game didn't cost them as much either its mostly recycled assets from Titanfall 2 otherwise EA would never have allowed it to go F2P. The guns along with gunplay in it sucks and ammo is to low and runs out to quickly too.  

Unless u really like battle royale the game sucks and is a slap in the face to Titanfall fans and even if you like battle royale there's better out there crap Pubg is a hell of alot better in my opinion.

comment: Am I the only person in the world who actually hates this game? First of all, its very well made and optimised. It has wonderful movement and graphics and the guns are a lot of fun. So why do I hate it then? It takes way too many God damn bullets to down someone and God forbid kill them. And yes I'm talking getting headshots, not missing and them not having shields up while down. It seriously takes way too long. And here's the biggest issue. I'm a long time halo player as well as many other games. So I'm not unfamiliar with long ttk. However in halo for the most part everyone is on an even playing field. So the ttk isnt just for me but everyone else. In this game if I have an SMG and they have a shot gun I might as well just quit because I've literally dumped 3 mags into someone to kill them with the smgs and I've had times someone unaware of me after getting absolutely lit the fuck up can turn around with a shotgun or a hand cannon and kill me in 2 to 3 shots. AND YES. I get this is battle royale. But God damn the weapon balance is broken. I've gotten many wins in blackout/pubg etc. And no matter what gun I'm using in those aside from range limitations, superior skills wins you the fight. In this game, its do I have an SMG and can't find any other guns? Oh I do? Ok bend over and take it up the ass. Even some of the assault rifles are absolute garbage. And don't get me started on snipers. 5 shots upper chest with one or 2 headshots and they still don't even go down. (With the triple take at least) seriously? Nah. Not for me. I don't like hand holding forgiving games. Not to mention I've gotten so use to games like r6s where a headshot actually seems to matter. I  just dont have the patience to waste minigun levels of ammo to even get a kill.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @thecooljohn100
comment: A lot of the critiques you brought up are so opinion based. Like there being "too much different types of loot" in the game which I don't feel is the case at all. Compared to something like fortnite, it has way less variety of loot. It's on par with the amount of guns and attachments in blackout or pubg. Either way I think this game is really neat and fun with friends and people should give it a shot before listening to a kind of shitty review of it like this. I really doubt he played the game enough to really understand it, whereas I've been playing the game nonstop since launch and I don't think there are any huge problems with the game. I'm sure they'll release a balance patch soon and start adding more content in the months to come so hop on now for a really fun ride with this game.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @pristineo
comment: As a hardcore epic gamer, i personally love this game. I was masters in ow which is pretty good, but it felt too team oriented, and wayyy too buggy. The movement in this game feels really good and makes the aiming aspect very difficult since you strafe instantly. Perfect for noob stomping, the game is free. Mechanics like these make the game more hardcore, but as of lately it feels like most studios are caving to the normies who cry because they can't learn. The map design is amazing, all the different locations have unique win conditions and map geometry. Shooting feels good, I kind of wish the bullet drop was more like pubg and less like blackout, idk just a personal thing. Only problem I've had so far is the hit registration is super inconsistent. I'm not tryna *ahem* flex on ya but honestly my boys at gameranx can't give good reviews on fps games, i still love then to death though. So i thought I'd give some insight from a tryhard caffeine addict.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @jgunner280
comment: I'm enjoying this game a bit more than I did when I just did a blind jump into others like Fortnite. Its got something about it, from the sci-fi world, to the squad connection that just hooks you right in. However its still missing something I think should be fundemental to the genre, and that's.... just a real fleshed out practice function. Bots, or even just a more elaborate bootcamp looking area that is easy to access. Something that lets you have a safe environment to try out a strange character's special, because you can't just dick around with that stuff out in the middle of the field when your death or give-away could be the downfall of your whole team that match. I get it, dedication, trial and error, and "git gud" are a part of the system, but I feel like a bot mode or training ground beyond the heavily scripted one with a mediocre gun range would make a world of difference.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @undead_corsair
comment:
I've certainly been enjoying it more than fortnite, still feel like they could've incorporated more of the titanfall mobility, wall-running and double jumping would make the combat stand out more from other battle royales. Also the map design feels a bit generic, every BR game seems to have these wide sprawling maps when I feel like a focus on verticality could be more interesting. A map with half the area of the current one but with a complex city and viaduct system stacked on top of a ground and subterranean level would be so much cooler, and would also work well with the tf mobility system.
Overall it's fine, but it isn't doing enough to change my outlook on the BR genre, I'd rather have just waited and paid for a full price Titanfall 3.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @dblevins343
comment: Not saying this is a bad game but it is missing the core mechanics from Titanfall. No Titans is obvious but for fans of the series the mobility is missing in Apex too. There is still sliding and no fall damage but that's where it ends. Titanfall is built on Titan combat and player mobility which consist of wall running, double jump and sliding. Now, you might say this game is only missing two parts of mobility then so what's the point? I understand why you might think that but these things are inseparable in Titanfall. Wall running lets you reach greater heights and traverse the map and intense speeds. Sliding lets you carry the momentum (bunny hopping) from wall riding to get you to the next wall or jump over long distances. Double jump can be used get an extra little bit of height to get you to the next level or travel just a little farther. With wall riding and double jump gone the game plays entirely different. Most encounters in Titanfall are close quarters because players can close the gap quickly while being very difficult to hit. A lot of the combat in Apex is medium distance and can become stale mates because neither side can close the gap that separates them. This isn't exactly a problem since that's how most BR modes work but it simply doesn't feel anything like Titanfall. The key factor missing is the movement. I can understand not including Titans. Taking down a squad of Titans when your squad doesn't have one would be a near impossible task. However, the movement that makes infantry combat special in Titanfall is missing almost entirely. Again, I'm not saying the game is bad. Respawn Entertainment doesn't make a bad game. I'm just saying the combat can't hold a finger to what Titanfall has which is truly special.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @unmeshbharali8722
comment:
there would be no point in solo mode because this game emphasizes more on the team play...each character is important and the team play is crucial...thereby the respawning gimmick. in a solo mode it will not be any different than that of any other BR games but with space age weapons...it'll feel repetitive in terms of a BR..for example-Lifeline...what would be the point of a medic if you only keep healing yourself. or wraith. for whom would you made those rifts for? yourself? there would be no point to that...the fact that every character has something to offer to other players is something unique among BR...I mean you can do solo. but that rush of reviving a teammate or trying to respawn a teammate so that you can win as a team is exhilarating.Even if the other teammates are unknown. i have won a few with unknown people and to be able to play with complete strangers and yet build a team play on the spot using the ping system is beautifully done. another feature that will be useless in solo is the ping system. do you really think sit's worth it by removing few of the good features of this game just so somebody can play solo?
I think not. But that's just my opinion. But great video btw, but i shall have to disagree with you on the solo mode

That feeling of being rewarded for your abilities, like Halo 3, getting 7 sword kills in a row for a helmet or what not. author: @azurius_
comment: i really expected a worse microtransaction style from EA. Lets see how the game keeps going against all the other BR games. Its the first BR I was actually able to enjoy more than like 3 games, mainly because I really enjoy the weapon handling and you almost always can find some good loot in any location. I also really like the ping-feature, all weapons atleast feel viable to use, the inventory system is incredibly smooth for a BR, and I like that the lootboxes only drop cosmetics and stuff. Lets hope it generates enough revenue that EA doesnt just close the game next year and that the devs can go on develop this game.

author: @Urboyyycarlos
comment: Im a lvl 27 and i earned mirage at around 23,so roughly 20 to 23 lvls to earn 12,000 tokens,next ill buy caustic,and so on. The great hit detection is a huge plus against blackout/3arcs horrible hit detection. Although the game is turning mainstream which eventually ruins the experience because like many others..people ruin the meta/abuse certain bugs and glitches. But so far the game as a BR f2p,is one of the best out there,especially for the team/quality of life ui and gameplay,its insane that because ea didn't actually do anything for this other than publish it,shows why its best to let studios improve and handle their own ip rather than ruin a whole franchise or product for extra $. The game is a 8.5 for me,minor crashes/bugs such as blue screens,freezing,and party errors caused by the servers,nothing abit of timed patches wont fix.

comment: Even if you are sick of Battle Royales games, you should play/try this one. I've put countless hours in numerous BRs and this feels nothing like the usual. It doesn't even really feel like a Battle Royale. The way the map is designed creates a lot of chokepoints where very cool fights can take place, no fear of being out in the open and getting instakilled by someone preying on you like in PUBG and Blackout. The ''Legends'' adds alot of variety to the game and they all have very distinctive playstyles, but aren't necessarily reliant on their abilities like in other hero shooters like Overwatch.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @jedimaster0667
comment:
I loved Titanfall 2. It was a solid shooter. Everything just worked. And knowing that some of the people at respawn came from modern warefare 2 makes me put alot of faith in whatever they do because modern warefare 2 reigned supreme as a shooter for many years and gamers still talk about the good times had online in that game. 
I don't personally like the battle Royal craze. Seems alittle overhyped. However apex legends is a great addition to that market. Ofc being free to play is an excellent bonus. But alot of the Titanfall assets and control style is present in apex legends. So if you had fun with Titanfall you'll most likely have fun with apex legends. Minus the wall running. And because there is no wall running this game really feels like a modern warefare game with Titanfall guns and time to kill. That's another thing. The time to kill is longer than your average shooter these days. Which means you have a chance to come out on top even if you didn't get first shot. Which I would argue was the most compelling aspect of the Halo series before Halo 4 and 5. The time to kill in halo 2 and 3 was not super long but it wasn't super short. It was very strategic in handling the controls and knowing which weapon to use. There is an element of skill when the time to kill isn't instantaneous. However I would say it's almost impossible to take on 2 or 3 players in apex legends solo. But I guess that makes sense because they want to promote the team style play with the specialized characters and abilities. At first apex legends seems very balanced this way. No guns seem overpowered. Time to kill is reasonable. Promoting teamwork to win the game. Honestly I would pay $25 to download this game. If they launched an open beta for us to try first. But I'm glad they made it free to play. I'm not sure how they made that possible but I'm glad respawn is contributing to the game community rather than trying to suck the life out of it at every corner like some other... Companies we know.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @skyfiredraco
comment:
When i first heard of this game coming out of the blue i was actually quite a bit disappointed. No titanfall 3. A battle royale game in the titanfall universe... with no titans... and no wall running... wtf...

Also the speed at which it was announced and released gave me some serious Radical Heights flashbacks.

But i figured i'd try it. I mean... it's free... might as well get in on the ground floor of the memes right?

...

This thing is actually a lot of fun lol. 

Dropped about 5 hours into it on the first night i played and, while i suck at it... horribly... i actually enjoyed myself quite a bit. The classes are diverse. The weapons and weapon mods are different enough to be fun (even if they do fall into standard archetypes like smg, shotgun, sniper, etc.). Even without wall running the game feels very agile and fast too. 

And btw... that ping system? Everyone else in the genre needs to STEAL THAT PING SYSTEM. It feels like such a simple little type of thing but it makes no-mic squad play so, so much better. Yes, people in a group with full-on voice chat is still going to be better... but this is the first time i've ever played a battle royale game where i can turn things down because the kids are sleeping and NOT feel like dead weight in a game. Seriously... Epic... Activision... Look at this little ping system... 

Oh, and on a final note: can i at least say how nice it is to get a multiplayer game released that ISN'T a buggy mess for once? It isn't perfect but it actually feels pretty darn polished and with a minimum of bugs for just being released. In a world with Fallout 76 and the Anthem beta tests that almost feels novel lol.

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @MonkeyPowerkey
comment: It's nice every now and then to hear someone talk about a Battle Royale without just saying it's trash and should die and burn in hell because it's the worst thing ever and they hate it more then the man that kill their mother 5 years ago. It's kinda tragic to be honest the hate that Battle Royale gets. It's been relevant for a couple years now? And allready it's the most hated game type ever? The only thing Battle Royale needs is to be pushed a bit. It's not a terrible game idea. It's just one that hasn't been pushed to it's fullest potential. Anyways, i honestly think most of the hate comes from the fact that hating Fortnite has become the most trendy thing among angsty teens and adults who can't relise that growing up is a natural part of life to hate. Fortnite isn't being hated because it does much harm or is so fucking terrible. It's just how people get to feel relevant and cool these days. The fact is, if you don't like a game you generaly just don't play it. But there's sadly alot of people out there that don't feel like they belong. So they need to find a group of people they can feel at home with. And hate groups are a nice place to fit in because you only need to hate on something to be accepted. Some of these groups grow out of the boy band phase and become a little too big and then you end up with the people who hate Fortnite. And Fortnite + Battle Royale is a thing so therefor Battle Royale is in their eyes cancer. Honestly it's the hate community around it that is cancer. There needs to be a reason to hate on something this much... Fortnite isn't the death of gaming. There are other things more worthy of your hate. But oh well, people be simple creatures i guess. I'll check this one out when i get the time. I'm not really into Multiplayer games. But when there's a free game that looks OK i have no excuse not to try it. + I'm allways looking for that ONE Battle Royale game that nails what i'm looking for. Something non of them have so far. Atleast non of the ones i've tried.

comment: they needed to make it more titanfall though. there is nothing like the movement of titanfall 2. if they had that in this battle royale mode, that would have been amazing because it would speed up the game play. the grind of having to find gear is what most people of tired of imo because it slows down the game. it drags it. titanfall has always been about using different play styles to win the game. you could wall run and do awesome parkour to get around other players. soaring through the sky with grenade launchers was the thing. for a bit then players started to realize the counter was heavy hitting guns then they had to change up to snipers and so on. it was dynamic and relied on skill and parkour to get things done. that would be amazing in a battle royale setting. i hope they plan to make a game mode like that. the movement to speed up the game and really get the chance to be new in the battle royale setting. it would give us a reminder of Colosseum mode that was so loved but so forgotten...

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @KJawesome5
comment:
This is the first BR(Battle Royal) that I genuinely enjoy and I think the main thing is how it’s a shooter before it’s a BR in that most the primarily BRs I’ve played have shitty gunplay, horrendous weapon balancing, or just don’t play like a shooter should in combat, but this game truly has some really good feeling guns to it and most the guns seem pretty balanced compared to their counterparts 

tho I will say the pump shotgun dominates in close quarters and most of the pistols are completely unusable compared to the other guns but still take up the same slot 

Jake hit most of the good points but I really just want to emphasize 
1. The respawn mechanic really makes it so you’re invested in your team and you you end up with more good games than bad because of this
2. The ping system is so good it’s almost better than voice chat because it’s adaptive, so if you target an enemy it marks an enemy but if you target a piece of equipment it marks it and your character will give a basic description of it to the team, and really makes playing with randoms so much better

3. The characters are what really set this game apart since it seems to be the first successful BR to incorporate different characters that are all separate but still balanced enough that each of them are fun to play yet they aren’t so integral to the game that if you don’t get to play your fav character you’re not going to have fun playing, and I usually enjoy big personality characters that are each unique and have a lot to say or show about themselves but this game hits a good middle ground in that they aren’t just constantly spouting exposition about their back story but their personality still comes through in small quotes and lines as well as how they say things when they interact in the environment

And that’s just my 2 cents but with so many pros and the fact that it’s free there’s no reason not to at least try Apex out even if you normally hate BRs you’ll probably have a great time with this gem

Thanks for reading all this I’m just really excited and hyped for this game :)

title: Apex Legends - Before You Buy
author: @urgarb9718
comment:
I think the problem with Battle Royale game is more than just “there’s too many” and “companies are just getting on the hype train”. While this is true, I think the major problem is the players. As the game ages, so does the players skill.That means that the game becomes less friendly to new players. Take fortnite as an example. At the beginning, people had a pretty equal chance of winning and could have genuine fun. Now, you have to now all the games new mechanics, and keep grinding as the other players to be on their level to have a chance of getting kills and a victory. Now going against players, players have gotten so good and so close in power gaps, that every battle becomes a full exertion(tryhard against tryhard), meaning it doesn’t become fun, but just focusing. It gets repetitive and tiring. This can be seen through Battle Royale’s (a long with a few others) lifespan. This ultimately contributes to killing it, since it doesn’t become fun anymore (what games are supposed to be. Sure tank division can work, but not to solve the whole problem. Eventually, players will go against their same skill level (maybe not at the beginning) every single time, to a point where it can get repetitive. Going against someone who is similar in skill to you can be amazingly fun, but there’s a fine line between focusing and having to go tryhard every time to gain a single advantage. Another great example is defaults in fortnite, they can provide humor and a relief from all the fighting. I think that is the flaw of Battle Royale games



Sorry I went full essay mode on y’all

author: @ItsJustRyansChannel
comment: Big props to Respawn. I had high hopes for them with how well they improved on Titanfall 2 compared to the first game. It was like night and day. They really listen to the players and fans know how to give us what we like. Apex Legends is great fun. Love the focus on squad based play. Considering I despise games like PUBG and fucking Fortnite (god, I don’t even wanna say the name of the game), Apex is right up my alley. This is the Battle Royale game for the rest of us. For all the gamers that resisted the Battle Royale trend and refused to give in and play childish crap like Fortnite or convoluted crap like Call of Duty’s Blackout. For every gamer that feels like punching a baby in the face every time you see someone do a “Fortnite dance”, this game’s for you. Enjoy.

comment: So far, I've loved Apex Legends (most of my friends shorten it down to Apex). But as a huge Titanfall fan, and one whose dabbled in multiple BR games, I have found Apex to really be the most unique. I love the streamlined systems, and the slides are super satisfying. Hopefully they add an item, or legend, to allow wallrunning in certain scenarios. As for what I've been playing, Wraith has been my go to, as I love getting ganks on players. And I've been putting my portal down after engagements, so we can loot and get closer to the circle faster.
